om minor to major mergers accentuates\nthese effects. When the spin vectors of the galaxies prior to the dry merger\nare misaligned, $j_{\\rm stars}$ decreases to a greater magnitude, while in wet\nmergers co-rotation and high orbital angular momentum efficiently spun-up\ngalaxies. We predict what would be the observational signatures in the $j_{\\rm\nstars}$ profiles driven by dry mergers: (i) shallow radial profiles and (ii)\nprofiles that rise beyond $\\approx 10\\,r_{50}$, both of which are significantly\ndifferent from spiral galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Jan 2017 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Oct 2017 15:04:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-13"}
