. In\nthis paper, we describe the design, construction, and test of the telescope\nstructure, as well as its performance during a 25-hour flight from Ft. Sumner,\nNew Mexico. The carbon fiber-aluminum composite structure met the requirements\nset by X-Calibur and its design can easily be adapted for other types of\nexperiments, such as X-ray imaging or spectroscopic telescopes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Jan 2017 05:48:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-18"}
